Package us.ihmc.euclid.utils

Class NameBasedHashCodeTools

  • java.lang.Object
    • us.ihmc.euclid.utils.NameBasedHashCodeTools
  • public class NameBasedHashCodeTools
extends java.lang.Object
    NameBasedHashCodeHolder provides a series of tools to calculate String based unique hash codes in addition to some default values.

    Use these tools with NameBasedHashCodeHolder to ensure name based hash codes are calculated using the same algorithm.

        public static long computeArrayHashCode​(NameBasedHashCodeHolder[] holders)
        Combines the hash codes from each of the holders to calculate a new name based hash code that represents the given array.

        Returns:
        the combined unique hash code.

      • computeSubArrayHashCode

        public static long computeSubArrayHashCode​(NameBasedHashCodeHolder[] holders,
                                           int firstIndex,
                                           int lastIndex)
        Combines the hash codes from each of the holders ∈ [ firstIndex, secondIndex ] to calculate a new name based hash code that represents the sub-array.
        Parameters:
        holders - the objects which hash codes are to be combined. Not modified.
        firstIndex - index of the first object to use for computing the combined hash code.
        lastIndex - index of the last object to use for computing the combined hash code.
        Returns:
        the combined unique hash code.

      • computeStringHashCode

        public static long computeStringHashCode​(java.lang.String string)
        Computes the unique hash code from the given string.

        The hash code is computed using String#hashCode() when the object is not null. If the object is null, this method returns 0L.

        Parameters:
        string - the string to compute the hash code of.
        Returns:
        the string hash code.
